text: The 1926 North Dakota gubernatorial election was held on November 2, 1926. Incumbent Republican Arthur G. Sorlie defeated Democratic nominee David M. Holmes with 81.74% of the vote. ==Primary elections== Primary elections were held on June 30, 1926. ===Democratic primary=== ====Candidates==== *David M. Holmes, businessman ====Results==== ===Republican primary=== ====Candidates==== *Arthur G. Sorlie, incumbent Governor *James M. Hanley, former North Dakota District Court Judge *J. A. McGovern ====Results==== ==General election== ===Candidates=== Major party candidates *Arthur G. Sorlie, Republican *David M. Holmes, Democratic Other candidates *Ralph Ingerson, Farmer–Labor ===Results=== ==References== 1926 North Dakota Gubernatorial
title: 1926 North Dakota gubernatorial election
